para_trans: Maharashtra Development Service, Additional CEO / Project Director,
Sriman from Group-A (S-25) cadre. Vaishali Rasal replaced
GOVERNMENT ORDER NUMBER: MOVISA-1024 / Q.No. 267/2024 AASTA-3

In accordance with the provisions of the Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees for the Purpose of Public Service and Prevention of Delay in the Performance of Government Duties Act, 2005, with the approval of the authorities competent to make the transfer and in accordance with the provisions of sections 4 (4) and 4 (5) of the said Act, the Maharashtra Development Services, Group-A Cadre, has been constituted. The Government is transferring and posting of Vaishali Rasal, Project Director, District Rural Development Agency, ZP Yavatmal. The officer concerned is being posted in the position indicated in column no. 3 in front of his name.

02. The said order comes into immediate effect and the officer concerned shall join the post indicated in the order of posting forthwith. Also, the officers concerned should not go on unauthorised leave. The attention of the concerned authorities is being drawn to the Government Circular No: CDR 1082/2567/28 XI, dated 30.08.1982 of the General Administration Department. They should note that if the officers concerned submit any form of application for change of posting / cancellation of appointment, they will be liable for disciplinary action as per the instructions in the said Government Circular.
03. The concerned Divisional Commissioner / CEO, Zila Parishad shall ask the officer posted to join immediately in place of his / her appointment.

para_trans: GOVERNMENT ORDER NUMBER: NO. MOVISA-1024 / Q. NO. 267/2024 ASHTA-3

The officer concerned shall appear at the place of the new appointment and inform the Government of the date of assumption of office. If the officer concerned fails to join the post established within the prescribed time, the concerned CEO, Zila Parishad shall submit a proposal for disciplinary action against the said officer to the Government through the Divisional Authorities.
This Government Order is available on the website of the Government of Maharashtra www.maharashtra.gov.in.
